description:
File: rust/lichen-node/src/hybrid.rs:344-352

When a route discovery is already active for a destination, start_discovery returns the original RREQ without checking if the discovery state has advanced:

```rust
pub fn start_discovery(&mut self, dst: [u8; 16], now_ms: u32) -> Rreq {
    // Check if discovery already active
    if self.active_discoveries.iter().any(|d| d.destination == dst) {
        // Return existing RREQ
        let discovery = self.active_discoveries.iter()
            .find(|d| d.destination == dst)
            .unwrap();
        return discovery.discovery.rreq();
    }
    // ... create new discovery
}
```

The RREQ returned may be from the initial ring (TTL=1), but the discovery may have already advanced to ring 2 or 3 (TTL=2, 4, 8). Broadcasting the stale RREQ wastes airtime without making progress.

Fix: Either return the current ring's RREQ, or return None to indicate discovery is already in progress.
